        p Ray Charles died on June 10, 2004 because he was suffering from liver disease. During his lifetime he performed more than 10,000 concerts and recorded more than 60 albums. Ray Charles possessed one of the most recognizable voice in American music and his unique music inspired many other artists like Elvis Presley and Stevie Wonder.
